p: The last two axes consider different levels of prevalence and viral suppression at the start of the intervention. These factors represent the most basic ways that HIV epidemics are different between populations. The “low” levels are 1% and 0% for prevalence and viral suppression respectively while the “high” levels are 50% for both prevalence and viral suppression. The parameters for all scenarios are given in Table 3 (units are per month).
